<h1>Josh Haden</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://joshhaden.com/now">joshhaden.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Los Angeles
CA
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Singer/Songwriter
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I make compelling and hopefully entertaining music about love, sex, birth, death, life, freedom, confinement, and lemon trees.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I was invited to get my Masters in Philosophy years ago but I turned it down. I thought about going to law school as well. I have no choice in the matter.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
There is no longer any overbearing motif for the recording of music. There’s no need for a lot of money to make a great sounding album. With the collapse of the music business comes a lot of broke musicians but also a lot of freedom that didn’t exist previously.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
“The Circle” by Dave Eggers
</p>

